3. Trigger Conditions

Claude performs a Git update when any of the following happen:

User submits a new daily journal

User edits an existing journal

Claude completes a segmentation pass

Claude updates Remember or Rewire

User explicitly says â€œsaveâ€ or â€œcommitâ€

4. Pre-Commit Validation (MANDATORY)

Before committing, Claude must check:

Date uniqueness

No duplicate date blocks in Review/Journaling.md

Sentence integrity

No journal sentence modified

Folder discipline

Macro/Micro/Nano only in Review

Painway/Pathway only in Recognise

Traceability

Every Recognise entry links back to Review content

If validation fails â†’ abort commit and ask user

5. Commit Scope Rules

Claude must:

Modify only files affected by the current operation

Never rewrite past unrelated dates

Never reorder historical content

6. Commit Granularity
Single Journal Entry = One Commit

Each date submission results in:

1 commit

All related file updates included together

This guarantees:

Clear timeline

Easy rollback

Accurate history

7. Commit Message Format (STRICT)

Claude must use structured commit messages.

Format
